Okechukwu Nnodim, Abuja The Lagos-Ibadan standard gauge rail project is 90 per cent complete, the Federal Government said on Thursday. Outgoing Permanent Secretary, Federal Ministry of Transportation, Sabiu Zakari, said this at the ministryâ€™s headquarters in Abuja while handing over to a new Permanent Secretary, Hussaini Adamu. Presenting his stewardship at the ministry, Zakari expressed happiness that it was during his tenure that cardinal projects such as Abuja-Kaduna light rail train service was completed and put to use. Zakari, in a statement issued by the ministry, stated that the Lagos-Ibadan standard gauge railway was 90 per cent completed, adding that what remained was the point linking the rail line to Apapa ports. He said the Itakpe-Warri railline which was abandoned for over 30 years was completed while he worked at the ministry, adding that test runs were currently ongoing on the facility. Copyright PUNCH.
